        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-19T19:54:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e These data are tricky because \"untriaged\" could mean a digest with no associated expectation, or a digest with an expectation labeled \"untriaged\". Let\u0027s make it as simple as possible for the reader to clearly see all these nuances.\n\nNo, these two cases do not differ from the perspective of cleanup.\n\nmakeThreeDevicesDigestCounterByTest() is defined in this test - is that not what you meant?\n\nI don\u0027t think the expectations for three_devices needs to or should be defined in this test. We can discuss this offline if you prefer.",
      "parentUuid": "ffa75d70_272710cd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 75,
        "startChar": 37,
